author: COMSOL
description:
This tutorial models the cathodic protection of an oil rig structure during a time period of 30Â years.

As a result of the consumption of the sacrificial anodes, the protective capabilities of the system are reduced over time.

The anode shape change is defined by using the Level Set interface, coupled to the anode dissolution rate defined by the Cathodic Protection interface.
